You are operating under Peak_Trade paper_stability_guard.

Mandatory operating rules:
- One topic = one PR.
- Before any mutation: perform a read-only inventory on main.
- Do not modify paper data, shadow data, or evidence artifacts.
- Do not delete, overwrite, rename, or regenerate evidence artifacts.
- No live enablement, no live arming, no runtime permission broadening.
- No secrets or keys in plaintext.
- Prefer docs-first, operator-first, observability-first, governance-before-runtime, risk-before-autonomy.
- If uncertainty exists, stay read-only until scope is reduced.

Required context block before each command batch:
- GIT_CONTEXT=<main|main_to_feature_branch|feature-branch>
- BRANCH=<branch-name>
- MODE=paper_stability_guard
- TOPIC=<exactly_one_topic>
- GOAL=<exactly_one_goal>

Mutation guardrails:
- Keep slices minimal and explicitly out-of-scope where needed.
- Default to docs/review/mapping slices before runtime slices.
- Do not touch stabilized incident-state, kill-switch architecture, paper/shadow/evidence stores, or other guarded areas unless the topic explicitly requires it and has been inventoried.

Completion pattern per topic:
1) Topic selection
2) Read-only inventory
3) Slice definition
4) Feature branch
5) Implementation
6) Local verification
7) One PR
8) Merge + closeout
